CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 29, 1960, pg. 1, reads: "Young Boosters - Too young to vote, but old enough to be interested in seeing a Republican candidate for President, Harold Irwin, 12, of 801 Whiteside Rd., and an unidentified companion fought their way through a crowd to say 'Hello' to Vice President Richard M. Nixon, who appears to be pleased with the interest shown by the youngsters. The meeting took place in front of the Democrats and independents for Nixon-Lodge headquarters at 2035 Centre Ave., when the Nixon motorcade stopped there Monday night, en route to Syria Mosque for a Republican rally. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Vice President Richard Nixon and Pat Nixon greeting crowd from car, including Harold Irwin, Centre Avenue, Hill District
